    "Acceptance Criteria": {
      "id": "n%5BD%7C",
      "type": "rich_text",
      "rich_text": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": {
            "content": "AC1 Recitation: add or extend co-located tests around sessionModeConfig/session route behavior so recitation is included in config/opening-copy coverage and mode=recitation uses the recitation title, subtitle, placeholder, and opening behavior rather than freeform/review fallback.\nAC2 Guess Who play integration: add QuizPlayScreen tests for a wrong final free-text Guess Who attempt and a final skip path; assert /check receives answerMode, finalAttempt, and cluesUsed, the server correctAnswer is captured for wrong final attempts, and the completion payload records the final result with answerGiven, correct=false, cluesUsed, and answerMode.\nAC3 Dispute payload: add a test that disputes a non-final wrong quiz answer, then finishes or saves the round, and assert completeRound receives disputed:true on that question result.\nAC4 History label: add a positive QuizHistoryScreen test for a vocabulary round whose theme contains a supported language prefix; assert the row label includes Vocabulary: <Language>.\nAC5 E2E: Save & Finish from the mid-round quit modal has deterministic e2e coverage. Home quiz-discovery e2e is either represented by the existing j26 Playwright spec or equivalent maintained e2e coverage; flow inventory must cite the maintained coverage.\nAC6 Docs: update docs/flows/mobile-app-flow-inventory.md so QUIZ-14 no longer claims None if current code-level coverage proves the difficulty-bump banner; keep QUIZ-05 and QUIZ-16 coverage notes aligned with actual tests.",
            "link": null
          },
          "annotations": {
            "bold": false,
            "italic": false,
            "strikethrough": false,
            "underline": false,
            "code": false,
            "color": "default"
          },
          "plain_text": "AC1 Recitation: add or extend co-located tests around sessionModeConfig/session route behavior so recitation is included in config/opening-copy coverage and mode=recitation uses the recitation title, subtitle, placeholder, and opening behavior rather than freeform/review fallback.\nAC2 Guess Who play integration: add QuizPlayScreen tests for a wrong final free-text Guess Who attempt and a final skip path; assert /check receives answerMode, finalAttempt, and cluesUsed, the server correctAnswer is captured for wrong final attempts, and the completion payload records the final result with answerGiven, correct=false, cluesUsed, and answerMode.\nAC3 Dispute payload: add a test that disputes a non-final wrong quiz answer, then finishes or saves the round, and assert completeRound receives disputed:true on that question result.\nAC4 History label: add a positive QuizHistoryScreen test for a vocabulary round whose theme contains a supported language prefix; assert the row label includes Vocabulary: <Language>.\nAC5 E2E: Save & Finish from the mid-round quit modal has deterministic e2e coverage. Home quiz-discovery e2e is either represented by the existing j26 Playwright spec or equivalent maintained e2e coverage; flow inventory must cite the maintained coverage.\nAC6 Docs: update docs/flows/mobile-app-flow-inventory.md so QUIZ-14 no longer claims None if current code-level coverage proves the difficulty-bump banner; keep QUIZ-05 and QUIZ-16 coverage notes aligned with actual tests.",
